dct_title_s: Map of the Yukon or Kwich-Pak River [cartographic material] : to illustrate Mr. Whymper's paper / constructed and drawn by J. Arrowsmith. (raster)
dct_description_sm: Relief shown by hachures. Depth of Norton Sound depths are shown by soundings. Major Indian [Alaska Native] territories are shown. Includes inset of Behring Sea, North Pacific Ocean, Alaska, and Siberia. From: The Journal of the Royal Geographical Society of London. Vol. 38, (1868), p. 219-37; held in Firestone Library. Call number: G7 .J687 v.38 1868
dct_publisher_sm: London : published for the Journal of the Royal Geographical Socy. by J. Murray, Albemarle Strt., 1868.
dct_subject_sm: Yukon River (Yukon and Alaska)—Discovery and exploration
